<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="529" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,150,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,399,150,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="529">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
The median gonocoxites of the hypandrium are square and they present a hypandrial bristle on each side (
<figureCitation box="[302,423,186,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1496,1520]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,460,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-156@6.[151,1436,452,1472]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Scanning electron micrographs of D. austrosaltans male terminalia. (A) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia (512 x magnification). (B) Ventral view of aedeagus (1.310 x de magnification). (C) Ventral view of aedeagus and hypandrium (676 x magnification). (D) Lateral view of aedeagus and phallapodeme. Arrow heads = chitinized crests on the aedeagal sheath (707 x magnification). The imagens are from A2 strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649968/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="529">Fig. 4A, C</figureCitation>
). The aedeagal apex displays a punctiform dorsal protuberance, called aedeagal apical crest (
<figureCitation box="[160,278,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1496,1520]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,460,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-156@6.[151,1436,452,1472]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Scanning electron micrographs of D. austrosaltans male terminalia. (A) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia (512 x magnification). (B) Ventral view of aedeagus (1.310 x de magnification). (C) Ventral view of aedeagus and hypandrium (676 x magnification). (D) Lateral view of aedeagus and phallapodeme. Arrow heads = chitinized crests on the aedeagal sheath (707 x magnification). The imagens are from A2 strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649968/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="529">Fig. 4B, C</figureCitation>
); and this structure as well as the aedeagal apex are covered by scales (
<figureCitation box="[1056,1143,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1496,1520]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,460,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-156@6.[151,1436,452,1472]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Scanning electron micrographs of D. austrosaltans male terminalia. (A) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia (512 x magnification). (B) Ventral view of aedeagus (1.310 x de magnification). (C) Ventral view of aedeagus and hypandrium (676 x magnification). (D) Lateral view of aedeagus and phallapodeme. Arrow heads = chitinized crests on the aedeagal sheath (707 x magnification). The imagens are from A2 strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649968/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="529">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). The aedeagal sheath also differs from the species mentioned above, because it has several serrated and strongly chitinized crests, arranged longitudinally, dorsally, and laterally (
<figureCitation box="[584,711,294,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1496,1520]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,460,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-156@6.[151,1436,452,1472]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Scanning electron micrographs of D. austrosaltans male terminalia. (A) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia (512 x magnification). (B) Ventral view of aedeagus (1.310 x de magnification). (C) Ventral view of aedeagus and hypandrium (676 x magnification). (D) Lateral view of aedeagus and phallapodeme. Arrow heads = chitinized crests on the aedeagal sheath (707 x magnification). The imagens are from A2 strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649968/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="529">Fig. 4B, D</figureCitation>
). The ventral postgonites extend along the ventral region of the aedeagus, being parallel in the initial portion and divergent at the end (
<figureCitation box="[945,1069,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1496,1520]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,460,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-156@6.[151,1436,452,1472]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Scanning electron micrographs of D. austrosaltans male terminalia. (A) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia (512 x magnification). (B) Ventral view of aedeagus (1.310 x de magnification). (C) Ventral view of aedeagus and hypandrium (676 x magnification). (D) Lateral view of aedeagus and phallapodeme. Arrow heads = chitinized crests on the aedeagal sheath (707 x magnification). The imagens are from A2 strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649968/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="529">Fig. 4C, D</figureCitation>
). The aedeagal ventral processes are thin and arranged parallel to each other (
<figureCitation box="[665,759,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1496,1520]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,460,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-156@6.[151,1436,452,1472]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Scanning electron micrographs of D. austrosaltans male terminalia. (A) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia (512 x magnification). (B) Ventral view of aedeagus (1.310 x de magnification). (C) Ventral view of aedeagus and hypandrium (676 x magnification). (D) Lateral view of aedeagus and phallapodeme. Arrow heads = chitinized crests on the aedeagal sheath (707 x magnification). The imagens are from A2 strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649968/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="529">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). The pregonites are short and each pregonite displays two bristles (
<figureCitation box="[247,338,402,428]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1496,1520]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,460,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-156@6.[151,1436,452,1472]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Scanning electron micrographs of D. austrosaltans male terminalia. (A) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia (512 x magnification). (B) Ventral view of aedeagus (1.310 x de magnification). (C) Ventral view of aedeagus and hypandrium (676 x magnification). (D) Lateral view of aedeagus and phallapodeme. Arrow heads = chitinized crests on the aedeagal sheath (707 x magnification). The imagens are from A2 strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649968/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="529">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
